{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17501847","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17501847"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:35:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:35:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1799"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1799","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1799"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.64,0.06,0.18,0.04,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1799"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"42060"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1799","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1799"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1799"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"27032"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"3390"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9078"},{"type":"tags","id":"9270"},{"type":"tags","id":"9528"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"10994"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3710"},{"type":"contributions","id":"4161"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"42060","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/42060"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 38-year-old  woman presents to the Emergency Department with a one day history of fever, right upper quadrant abdominal pain, and malaise. She has a medical history of dyslipidaemia and obesity. Her medications include the oral contraceptive pill and simvastatin. On examination her pulse rate is 105/min, blood pressure 90/50mmHg, and temperature 38.5\u00b0C. Her sclera are icteric and abdominal examination demonstrates tenderness in the right upper quadrant.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely causative organism?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Escherichia coli","Klebsiella","Enterococcus","Bacteroides fragilis","Enterobacter"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patients presentation is concerning for acute cholangitis, with Charcot\u0027s triad present of right upper quadrant pain, jaundice, and fever. There is a risk of this progressing to Reynolds\u0027 pentad with additional features of shock and altered mental status. Biliary obstruction is most commonly due to choledocholithiasis, which is most likely in this clinical scenario.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe most frequently isolated pathogens are gram-negative enteric organisms: \u003Cstrong\u003EEscherichia coli\u003C/strong\u003E (25-50%), \u003Cstrong\u003EKlebsiella species\u003C/strong\u003E (15-20%), and \u003Cstrong\u003EEnterobacter\u003C/strong\u003E (5-10%); along with gram-positive \u003Cstrong\u003EEnterococcus\u003C/strong\u003E (10-20%). Anaerobic bacteria such as \u003Cstrong\u003EBacteroides fragilis\u003C/strong\u003E and Clostridium perfringens are identified in approximately 15% of cases, and particularly if there has been previous biliary surgery or in the elderly population. This highlights the importance of empiric antibiotic therapy covering for gram-positive, gram-negative and anaerobic organisms.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Escherichia coli is the most common organism associated with biliary sepsis."],"references":["Ahmed M. Acute cholangitis - an update. World J Gastrointest Pathophysiol. 